author: bfoster
msg: - removed all the hard coded metadata fields and standardized it to the filemgr based metadata and what was specified in the MetadataListPcsMetFileWriter input XML files . . . which can now be more than one file.
- added a XML to java properties (i.e. property equals value) xslt file.

- removed StdMetadataDumpPcsMetFileWriter . . . because no there is no standard metadata that gets dumped, only metadata that is loaded . . . you have to specifically specify which metadata to dump now using the MetadataListPcsMetFileWriter . . . this was done to generalize the met writer for cross project compatibility and limit code modifications for such.
